1 AN ACT relating to protection from extreme weather conditions.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 278 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Extreme weather conditions" means a:
7 1. Day for which the National Weather Service has issued either an
8 Extreme Cold Warning or Excessive Heat Warning for the county in
9 which the customer resides; or
10 2. Period of natural disaster in the county in which the customer resides.
11 As used in this paragraph, "natural disaster" means any natural
12 disaster resulting in the declaration of a state of emergency under
13 KRS 39A.100 or 39B.070; and
14 (b) "Utility" has the same meaning as in KRS 278.010(3)(a) and (b).
15 (2) A utility shall not disconnect or suspend residential service to a customer's
16 residence during extreme weather conditions.
17 (3) The commission shall issue an order setting forth any applicable rules and
18 procedures required to implement this section.
